#
# --- Orange Pi Zero 2W DTS tweak: DROPPED (not needed) ---
# patches.armbian/0302-...-add-emac-sound converts ethernet to the Allwinner vendor
# sunxi-gmac + AC200 EPHY/codec. The Zero 2W has no ethernet port (WiFi-only via
# uwe5622) and FPV needs no audio; the patch also references a vendor GMAC driver we
# don't include. Excluded per "required modules only" — mainline's board DTS already
# provides HDMI display.
#
# --- UWE5622 WiFi driver — SNAPSHOT the fully-patched driver tree from the Armbian worktree ---
# Replaying the 18-patch version progression (v6.3 base + v6.9..v6.18 + Fix-missing-prototypes)
# is fragile on mainline: the shims conflict under patch fuzz (e.g. a hunk re-adds `static` an
# earlier shim already added). Instead capture the END STATE — the drivers/net/wireless/uwe5622/
# tree as it exists in the Armbian 6.18.35 worktree (all shims applied, compiles) — as one
# add-files patch, then wire it into the top-level Kconfig/Makefile. Kernel BT-core hunks are
# intentionally excluded (no BT use); the driver's own tty-sdio glue lives under uwe5622/ and is
# kept. Source files only (build artifacts / .orig excluded by the extractor).
snapshot: drivers/net/wireless/uwe5622
gen: uwe5622-wireless-makefile
gen: uwe5622-wireless-kconfig
#
# --- Operator NV12 video patches (repo-owned, rebased onto current patches.drm) ---
# Source: board/orangepi/zero2w/patches-src/ (NOT the Armbian userpatches dir), so the
# repo is self-contained. Forward-ported from the operator's 0099/0100 to match the
# current DE33 format array (0099) and cedrus capture-format list (0100).
local: 0099-de33-enable-nv12-vi-plane.patch
local: 0100-cedrus-prefer-linear-nv12.patch
